-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Execute following to forward port:

// My location of adb.exe. Home PC.
cd E:\Android\Sdk\platform-tools
// My location of adb.exe. Work PC.
cd C:\Users\michal.hornak\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\platform-tools

//command itself - tcp:localPcPort tcp:emulatorPort
adb forward tcp:12371 tcp:12371


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use case - App host game, SocketTest connects as a client:
1) Start server in anadroid app
2) Connect to 127.0.0.1:12371 (or other port which you forwarded android emulator port to).
3) Send 01|myNickname  (join game message)
- you should register in host Lobby
4) Send 03|myNickname (ready to play message)
- you should see that status of a player was switched to READY
5) Host can now start game via start button




